social_posts.post_text: Move over Bellagio Fountains, there’s a new Fountain show in town. We’re excited to announce our new residency with @AGTsuperstars in Las Vegas at @luxorlv!

Opening night for @AGTSuperstars is finally here! We’ve added 5 new hilarious and very talented clowns that will be joining the Human Fountains family for the show. We’ve been rehearsing nonstop for over a week now to make sure all streams were flowing strong, and can’t wait to spit in front of live audiences.  In honor of the occasion, we thought we’d give you a look behind the scenes at the first rehearsals. Prepare to see a bunch of grown men taking spitting water extraordinarily seriously! 

Thanks to @CirqueDuSoleil for giving us our own spitting gym to practice where Professor @KaufyBreak has been leading classes. 

Please give a warm welcome to our newest fountains:
🗣️💦: @jesse_highley 
🗣️💦: @robertryanlasvegas 
🗣️💦: @brettalters

At @agtsuperstars, every artist gets their own look from the makeup department. @kaufybreak from @humanfountains gives you a makeup tutorial of how Human Fountains get ready. Does anyone else have any makeup tips to share? Looks like he could use as much help as possible 🤣
Water you waiting for? Head on down to @agtsuperstars at @luxorlv!
BIG NEWS! We’ll be airing on @AGT Allstars this Monday, January 23 at 8pm ET/PT on @NBC. Excited for the world to see our latest spitting SPITacular! Tune in, because things are about to get wet 🗣️💦

Cameraman: “Tell the audience you’re performing on 
@AGT
: Allstars next week on Monday January 23rd at 8/7c on NBC so you can share it on social later on”

Us: *Look around at each other questionably, and then…..*

As we prepare to be on @AGT: Allstars, we wanted to relive our past America’s Got Talent appearances. 

Let’s start at the beginning, our 1st appearance at the audition rounds. While we worked hard to put this act together, we had no idea how it would be received. Our only goal was to not get kicked off the stage! 

We kicked things off with a bit of trickery by telling the judges we were there to sing opera.

We were terrified as we walked on stage to an audience of over 2,000 people. We had no performing background, & this was our first time on stage.

The act started & honestly, it’s all a bit of a blur, since we were so nervous, but we do remember a loud buzz as Simon gave us an X soon into the act. Nevertheless, we got through the rest of the act without being kicked off stage. That was our goal & we succeeded! 

BUT WAIT! After we finish we get a standing ovation from the entire crowd & judges as they chanted “Send them through.” Things seemed to have gone better than we expected…

It’s time for the judges to cast their votes. Three must say yes for us to move to the next round. Simon starts it off with a no, but Heidi & Mel both say yes. It was all up to Howie…. In a fairytale moment, Howie miraculously sends us through to the next round. We can’t believe it. Our goal was not to get kicked off the stage, & now we find ourselves headed to the next round. 

As we celebrated on stage, host & supermodel @TyraBanks comes on stage with her own bottle of water. We improvise a spitting act with her. As we all spat together, @KaufyBreak saw a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity. 

He waited for Tyra to take another sip of water & then ran over & pointed to his mouth. She took the hint & spat water straight in his mouth. Legend says he’s never brushed his teeth since. 

We got off stage in a daze of disbelief & happiness. It was then that the producers approached us & said, “That was great, we can’t wait to see what you have in store next!”

Gulp….. We looked at each other….. That was our only act. We had no other acts at this point. What the hell were we going to do that could top this? 

To Be Continued…

We don’t usually look forward to Monday…. But we’ll make an exception this time! 
Don’t miss as we air on @AGT: Allstars this Monday at 8/7c on NBC. Things are about to get wet 💦

#AGTAllStarsPremiere #AGTAuditions #AGTAllStars

As we prepare for our @AGT: Allstars appearance on Monday, we’ve been walking you through our past America’s Got Talent appearances. So where did we leave off? We’d just made it through the audition rounds and were headed to Judge Cuts. Let’s dive in…..

If our neighbors thought we were crazy before, now they thought we were insane. For hours they’d see a bunch of grown men standing on the driveway, blasting opera music, and spitting water, as we tried to step it up and create a new act.

We knew we couldn’t just spit to a new song, we had to bring it to the next level. So we decided to add a storyline.

We spent countless days putting the act together. We knew spitting in each other’s mouths shocked America once, but we’d have to think out of the box to shock people again. Some orange juice and an egg did just the trick. 

Yes, we did find it gross. But the more we rehearsed, the more numb we became to what’s gross for the average person.

After a month of rehearsing, it was finally time to head back and compete in the Judge Cut Round of America’s Got Talent. We felt out of place as we entered the studio on competition day seeing all our competitors with some of the top talents in the world. When people asked what we did, we’d look them straight in the eye and say: “Um, we spit water….”

We went out and performed our new act to the judges and a huge room of audience members. We got a very positive and loud reaction to it, and even another standing ovation, but also might have underestimated how much we’d gross out America…. We weren’t joking when we said we’d lost our sense of what people find gross. We were in too deep.

Later on we heard we’d made it through to the next round! The judges had given us the wild card spot to keep our AGT journey alive. We were ecstatic until the producers approached us backstage and said, “That was great, we can’t wait to see what you have in store for the next round!”

Déjà Vu.

We looked at each other just as we had after the first round…... We had no other acts. What the hell were we going to do that could top passing a raw egg between a group of guys? 

To Be Continued…

#AGTAllStarsPremiere #AGTAuditions #AGTAllStars
Which reaction do you think people will have after watching our @AGT: Allstars performance on Monday? 1, 2 or 3?

We’ll be on @AGT: Allstars this Monday! In honor of the occasion, we’ve been walking you through our past America’s Got Talent appearances. So where did we leave off? We were headed to the live shows for the Quarter-Finals. Let’s dive back into the story.

Some how we made it to the Dolby Theater, one of the most prestigious theaters in the world and home to the Academy Awards. And we were invited to spit on their floors…..

But hey, we weren’t going to let this opportunity go to waste. We went back to the drawing board and started creating a brand new act. This was a spectacle act. Our fountain moves were epic, our streams were stronger, and of course, we’d add a few surprises!

We were terrified as we got ready to perform live in front of all of America. But as the music started, we got to work and started spitting. Performing was a bit of a blur as we were so nervous, but once we were done we got our third standing ovation.

Later on we found out that we unfortunately didn’t make it through to the next round. Yes, we were a bit disappointed, but also grateful for the opportunity.

We thought our wet and wild journey was over. Little did we know, it was just beginning. After the show aired we began receiving offers from television shows around the world to come perform. For 2 years, we got to perform around the globe.

After doing this for a while, we wanted to take the next step. So we locked ourselves away for months and created a full Human Fountain show. 

We started getting some traction with the show as we performed it to live audiences. Then something called COVID-19 came along, and let us tell you….. COVID was not great for the spitting industry….. So we had to press pause there. At this point we got on TikTok. There we grew a following of over 1.2 million followers.

As COVID eventually calmed we were able to begin performing for live audiences again.

A few months laters, we were asked to be in a Las Vegas show, @AGTSuperstars. Where we have been performing our act. We’re still there today! 

We couldn’t be more excited for our appearance on AGT: Allstars this Monday.  If we get you to smile, we’ve done our jobs!
We’re getting ready for our @AGT: Allstars appearance TOMORROW at 8/7c on NBC! Bring your umbrella ☂️

Take a look at our latest fountain show that we performed on @AGT: Allstars! 

It’s our America act- our most patriotic fountain show yet. It pays tribute to some of the USA’s greatest traditions and symbols ⚾️🌭🎆🗽🇺🇸 How lucky are we to live in a country where we’re free to spit water!

This act is actually part of our full show, so we’ve been performing it for a while now to live audiences. However, we were so excited to get the opportunity to perform our America act on TV in front of…….well, all of America! 

No matter if you’re from the USA or another country though, we can all agree on one thing: everyone likes to laugh. We hope our silly act succeeds in putting a smile on your face! 🙂

We’ve been loving performing every night in Las Vegas at @AGTSuperstars. Which slogan should the show use? 1 or 2?

1) Come see the second best fountain show in Las Vegas!

2) Come see Heidi Klum and the Bellagio’s child!
